s subsidiary companies, directors, officers, employees, agents, and related entities<br>responsible for maintaining this Website make no claims, guarantees, or representations<br>regarding the accuracy of the information on the Website, the accuracy of information<br>provided by third parties linked to the site, or the accuracy of information on those linked<br>sites. While reasonable efforts have been made to ensure the accuracy of the information,<br>JWC Property Group Pty Ltd will not accept any liability for any loss or damage incurred by<br>any person acting in reliance on the information.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Privacy Policy<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In this Privacy Policy, references to &#8220;we,&#8221; &#8220;us,&#8221; and &#8220;our&#8221; denote JWC Property Group Pty<br>Ltd (ABN 19 616 974 086) and our Related Bodies Corporate, subsidiaries, affiliates<br>(collectively referred to as &#8220;<strong>JWC Property Group<\/strong>&#8220;), and their officers, employees,<br>volunteers, contractors, and agents.<br>By providing personal information to us, you consent to our collection, use, and disclosure<br>of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy (as amended from time<br>to time) and any other agreements between you and us. We may modify our Privacy Policy<br>and encourage you to periodically check our Website for updates.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<style>\n.li-padding li {padding-bottom: 30px}\n.li-padding li::marker {font-weight: bold}\n<\/style>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"li-padding wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Our Commitment to Your Privacy<\/strong><br><br>JWC Property Group Pty Ltd may collect your Personal Information in the course of<br>our business and is dedicated to safeguarding and respecting your privacy. This<br>Privacy Policy applies to all Personal Information collected by JWC Property Group<br>through the Website and outlines your rights in relation to accessing, updating, or<br>removing Personal Information. We adhere to the Australian Privacy Principles<br>(APPs) as defined in the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth)(the Act). You may obtain a copy of<br>the APPs from the website of The Office of the Australian Information Commissioner<br>at www.aoic.gov.au.<br> <\/li><li><strong>Definitions<\/strong><br><br>The following terms have the following meanings:<br>\u2022 Cookies: Small text files stored on a user&#8217;s computer or phone for record-keeping<br>purposes.<br>\u2022 Information: Refers to both Personal Information and Non-personal Information.<br>\u2022 Minors: Individuals below the age of 18 years.<br>\u2022 Non-personal Information: Information that does not reveal specific identity or<br>directly relate to an individual.<br>\u2022 Personal Information: Information or an opinion about an identified individual or<br>one who is reasonably identifiable, recorded in a material form, including but not<br>limited to name, address, email, phone number, age, financial information, and<br>other details.<br>\u2022 Services: Services provided by JWC Property Group to consumers.<br>\u2022 User, you, your: Refers to users of the Website and individuals who purchase<br>services or interact with JWC Property Group.<br> <\/li><li><strong>Why We Collect Your Personal Information<\/strong><br><br>We collect, use, and disclose your Personal Information for various business<br>purposes, aiming to enhance and expand our services while ensuring your safety and<br>efficiency. The specific types of Personal Information we collect may vary depending<br>on your role or engagement with JWC Property Group, including vendor, purchaser,<br>landlord, tenant, supplier, employee, agent, or independent contractor. Examples of<br>Personal Information we may collect include your name, email address, contact<br>details, age, financial information, transaction details, and more. Your consent is<br>generally required for this collection, and you have the option to refuse or provide<br>information anonymously or using a pseudonym. However, refusal to provide certain<br>information may affect our ability to provide requested services.<br><\/li><li><strong>How may Personal Information be used?<\/strong><br><br>We may use your Personal Information for purposes such as:<br>\u2022 Providing products and services, as well as communication.<br>\u2022 Monitoring and improving service quality.<br>\u2022 Communicating with prospective or actual vendors, purchasers, landlords, and<br>tenants.<br>\u2022 Enhancing Website performance and functionality.<br>\u2022 Understanding your needs through surveys, market research, and customer<br>loyalty programs.<br>\u2022 Handling privacy-related complaints and issues.<br>\u2022 Conducting research and analysis.<br>\u2022 Sending notifications about products, services, offers, promotions, or marketing.<br>\u2022 Conducting business processing functions, including sharing information with<br>related entities, contractors, service providers, advertisers, sponsors, or third<br>parties.<br>\u2022 Enforcing engagement terms and conditions.<br>\u2022 Performing credit checks (if applicable).<br>\u2022 Referring you to a mortgage broker or financier.<br>\u2022 Administrative, marketing, planning, product or service development, quality<br>control, survey, and research purposes.<br>\u2022 Complying with applicable laws, rules, regulations, and resolving disputes.<br>If you wish to access, correct, object to the use of, restrict, or delete your previously<br>provided Personal Information, you may contact us using the details in paragraph 14 below.<br>We will respond to your request promptly and in accordance with applicable law.<\/li><li><strong>Direct Marketing<\/strong><br><br>We and\/or third parties may send you direct marketing communications and<br>information, subject to your consent. These communications may include emails,<br>SMS, mail, or other forms of communication, complying with the Spam Act 2003 and<br>best practice guidelines. You can opt-out of receiving such communications at any<br>time through our Website, by emailing us at info@jwc.com.au, or through our JWC<br>Property Group client preference center within our direct emails. If you opt-out,<br>please note that your information may remain with third parties we have already<br>shared it with.<\/li><li><strong>How We Collect Your Personal Information<\/strong><br><br>We collect your Personal Information directly from you through various means,<br>including:<br>\u2022 General or specific telephone, email, onsite, or other inquiries.<br>\u2022 Communication and engagement with us, including attending open for<br>inspections, submitting details via the &#8216;Contact Us Today&#8217; page, and more.<br>\u2022 Providing your contact details.<br>\u2022 Accessing our Website or participating in online inquiries.<br>\u2022 Negotiating with us regarding property purchases or rentals.<br>\u2022 Completing transactions.<br>\u2022 Surveys, feedback, promotions, competitions, or interactions.<br>\u2022 Information submitted during discussions or engagements with us.<br>\u2022 Sharing information via social applications or services.<br>\u2022 Providing details such as ABN, ACN, financial information, employer details,<br>occupation, and property title and mortgage details.<br>We may also collect your Personal Information from third parties, publicly available<br>sources, and other sources connected to the services we provide.<\/li><li><strong>To Whom We Disclose Personal Information<\/strong><br><br>We may disclose your information to various parties, including our partners,<br>employees, affiliates, contractors, service providers, and third parties with whom we<br>have commercial relationships for business, marketing, and related purposes. Your<br>information may also be shared with third parties to provide services you requested,<br>as required by law, to enforce terms and conditions, or in connection with corporate<br>transactions such as business sales, mergers, or asset sales.<br>Third parties to whom we disclose Personal Information may have their own privacy<br>policies governing how they use and disclose this information.<\/li><li><strong>How to Complain About Privacy and Access, Correct, Update, Delete, or Exercise<br>Other Rights<\/strong><br><br>We take steps to ensure the accuracy, currency, and completeness of the Personal<br>Information we collect, and we will promptly correct any inaccuracies when notified.<br>If you wish to access, correct, or amend your Personal Information, please contact us<br>using the details in paragraph 14 below. We will respond as soon as reasonably<br>practicable and in compliance with applicable law.<br>If you have privacy-related complaints or concerns, please contact us in writing.<br>Details for contacting us can be found in paragraph 14. We will treat your complaint<br>as confidential and will resolve it as soon as possible, considering the nature and<br>complexity of the issues. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may escalate<br>your complaint to the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner.<\/li><li><strong>Non-personal Information<\/strong><br><br>We may collect Non-personal Information from the Website, including data on which<br>sections of the Website are frequently visited, usage duration, and related<br>information. This data is used in aggregate form and may be shared with our agents,<br>consultants, and employees to improve our services.<\/li><li><strong>Minors<\/strong><br><br>We do not knowingly solicit or collect Personal Information from individuals under<br>18 years of age. Parents or guardians are encouraged to prevent minors from<br>submitting Personal Information without prior permission.<\/li><li><strong>Website Use and Cookies<\/strong><br><br>We may use cookies or similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing<br>experience on our Website. These technologies help us recognize your browser and<br>track your interactions with the Website. Most web browsers are set to accept<br>cookies, but you can disable them, though it may affect your Website experience.<br>Authentication through social media accounts may provide us with Personal<br>Information linked to your account. Additionally, if you &#8216;like&#8217; or &#8216;follow&#8217; us on social<br>media, we may access your social media page.<br>You may be provided with a unique password for certain Website features, and you<br>are responsible for its secrecy. Notify us of any loss or unauthorized use of your<br>password.<\/li><li><strong>Security<\/strong><br><br>We take reasonable measures to protect Personal Information from misuse, loss,<br>unauthorized access, modification, or disclosure. However, we cannot guarantee the<br>security of information transmitted over the internet.<\/li><li><strong>Privacy and Website Changes<\/strong><br><br>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy from time to time, with the latest<br>version available on our Website. As the internet is inherently insecure, we cannot<br>guarantee the security of information communicated online, and transmission is<br>done at your own risk.<\/li><li><strong>Contact Us<\/strong><br><br>For inquiries about our privacy policy or further information on how we handle<br>Personal Information, please contact us using the following details:<br>\u2022 Email: info@jwc.com.au<br>\u2022 Phone: 03 9028 8592<br>\u2022 Postal Address: Shop 1, 209 Toorak Road, South Yarra VIC 3141<\/li><\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Terms and Conditions &amp; Privacy Policy Copyright All materials accessible through this Website are subject to copyright and are the exclusiveproperty of JWC Property Group Pty Ltd (ABN 19 616 974 086) and its affiliated entities. Noportion of these materials may be reproduced through any means, except as permitted bythe Copyright Act 1968. Website Access [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"com